values: 忙碌的；繁忙的；占线的（指电话）；正被占用的；热闹的；熙熙攘攘的

synonym.mean: 忙碌的；热闹的；正被占用的

pos_mean_info_list.mean: 喧闹；活跃；裙撑；热闹的活动

word_group.brief_definition: 忙碌的人生；繁忙的人生
繁忙的工作；忙碌的工作；工作忙

bilingual.target: 妈妈是一只忙碌的蜜蜂。
我度过了一个忙碌的周末。
这是一个非常忙碌的学期！

bilingual.source: Saturday was a busy day for me.
bilingual.target: 星期六对我来说是忙碌的一天。

bilingual.source: Toys and games that keep the hands busy have been popular for decades.
bilingual.target: 让手忙碌的玩具和游戏已经流行了几十年。

bilingual.source: After a busy day, I need to relax.
bilingual.target: 在忙碌的一天后，我需要放松一下。
她喜欢忙碌的都市生活方式。

bilingual.source: Yesterday was a very busy day for me.
bilingual.target: 昨天对我来说是非常忙碌的一天。

bilingual.source: Convenience food is very useful on busy days.
bilingual.target: 方便食品在忙碌的日子里非常有用。

bilingual.source: Instant noodles are convenient for busy days.
bilingual.target: 方便面很方便，适合忙碌的日子。

list.abstract: busy，音标[ˈbɪzi]，英语单词。作形容词为忙碌的、热闹的、电话线占线的等，作动词指的是忙于，作名词为警官、警察。例句：We're looking for Saturday assistants in our busy town centre restaurant.（我们繁忙的市中心餐馆正在招周六助理。） busy的近义词有engaged、abustle、employ，反义词有idle。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, I mean, God did take time out of his busy schedule to bless these Sloppy Joes. Come on, Shelly, tell me your news.
yingyinNormal.zh: 毕竟主可是从他忙碌的日程里抽空祝福了这些邋遢乔汉堡呢。说啊，谢利，发生什么事了。

yingyinNormal.en: So I'm going to use variations of dishes that my grandmother loved to cook for me to show a couple of busy mums two recipes that are quick and healthy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以我打算改良几道我奶奶爱为我做的菜，来给一些忙碌的妈妈们展示两款快速又健康的食谱。

yingyinNormal.en: Like most Beijingers, Zhang Yan leads a busy, modern life. But each spring, she and her family take a break to indulge in the traditions that make this time of year so special.
yingyinNormal.zh: 像大多数北京人，张岩过着忙碌的现代生活。但每年春季，她和她的家人会稍作休息沉湎在传统之中，令这段日子与别不同。

yingyinNormal.en: People, I am very busy today.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我今天很忙。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, dad? I'm kinda busy. What's up?
yingyinNormal.zh: 爸爸？我有点忙，怎么了？

yingyinNormal.en: You were so busy trying to be her, Riley.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你一心想着要变成她的样子，莱丽。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't leave now, Sheldon. I'm very busy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我现在走不开，Sheldon我很忙。

yingyinNormal.en: Keep busy, but avoid unnecessary exertion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 找点事做，但不要耗费过多精力。

yingyinNormal.en: What? I'm busy. It's Malky, man. He's dead.
yingyinNormal.zh: 怎么了？我现在很忙。是马尔奇，他死了。

yingyinNormal.en: You're a busy man. I don't know the opposite.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是个大忙人。我从来没闲下来过。

yingyinNormal.en: I guess I was just busy keeping them all alive.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我总是忙于让他们都活下去 所以忘记了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, gee, I don't know. My schedule's a little busy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可不知道有没有时间，我的日程有点满。

yingyinNormal.en: You've been busy. And you've been a complete idiot.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你没闲着啊。你好傻啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Because I'm too busy answering everybody's private requests for advice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为我正回复每个人的私信，给他们提建议，没空烦恼。

yingyinNormal.en: You have been busy, haven't you? Quite the busy little bee.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你一直还挺忙吧? 像小蜜蜂团团转。

yingyinNormal.en: Busy, isn't it? Busy? No. This is quiet for the Potato City. Have a lovely day.
yingyinNormal.zh: 挺热闹的，是吧？热闹吗？没有啊，今天的土豆城市已经算冷清的了。祝你们玩的愉快！

yingyinNormal.en: What busy bees. Yes, we're busy bees. Buzz. Now, we must fly back to our hive to make honey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好勤劳的蜜蜂啊。是的，我们是勤劳的小蜜蜂，我们现在要回到蜂箱去了，去酿蜂蜜。

yingyinNormal.en: Why are you calling me Mr. Grady? Owen. If you're not too busy. I'm pretty busy. We have an attraction.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你为什么叫我格雷迪先生？欧文，如果你不是很忙的话。我忙得很。我们遇到了一个问题[互相吸引]。

yingyinNormal.en: But now my dad's busy with his new wife, who was his old boss. And my mom, well, she's busy not getting over that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我爸爸现在和新妻子生活。爸爸的新妻子是他以前的老板。我妈妈忙着借酒消愁。

yingyinNormal.en: Goodness me. What do we have here? Granny. We're busy bees. Buzz. Ah. Would you busy bees like some toast? Yes, please.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢天啊，这是怎么回事呀？奶奶，我们是勤劳的蜜蜂。勤劳的蜜蜂们想来吃面包吗？是的。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: actively or fully engaged or occupied; occupied with or concentrating on a particular activity or object of attention

examination_example.sentence: Imagine you are pouring your heart out to someone and they are just <highlight>busy</highlight> on their phone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 想象一下，你正在向某人倾吐心声，而他们正忙着打电话。

examination_example.sentence: That everyone's too <highlight>busy</highlight> these days is a cliché.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如今每个人都太忙是老生常谈了。

examination_example.sentence: But as companies continue their attempts at personalised medicine, the courts will remain rather <highlight>busy</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但随着企业继续尝试个性化医疗，法庭将依然相当繁忙。

word_usage.usage: “忙于做某事”可以用be busy doing sth.表达，也可以用be busy with sth.表达。

word_family.mean: adj. 忙碌的；繁忙的；热闹的；杂乱的；忙音的；专注于…的；忙于…的；充满活动的；装饰过分的；电话线占线的

sense_info_list.en: actively or fully engaged or occupied; occupied with or concentrating on a particular activity or object of attention

examination_example.sentence: People are too <highlight>busy</highlight> thinking about what they can do to think about whether they should do it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们忙于考虑他们能做什么，而没有考虑他们是否应该去做。

examination_example.sentence: This would allow the casual user to save money and time, freeing up casual space in our <highlight>busy</highlight> lives to read a good book.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这将使休闲用户节省金钱和时间，从而在忙碌的生活中腾出休闲空间来阅读一本好书。

word_usage.usage:
说“某人工作忙”，应以人作主语。
示例：你工作很忙吗?
误 Is your work busy?
正 Are you busy with your work?

“表示忙于做某事”可以用be busy (in) doing sth.，介词in可以省略。
示例：She is busy (in) doing her homework.
她正忙着做自己的家庭作业。

examination_example.sentence: While remote workers help to keep the café full in quiet times, they can take up the valuable table space in <highlight>busy</highlight> periods.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然远程工作的人有助于保持咖啡馆在清闲时满座，但他们也会在忙碌时段占用宝贵的餐桌空间。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>busy</highlight> streets in Paris were uneven and caked in thick mud.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 巴黎繁忙的街道凹凸不平，满是厚厚的泥巴。

examination_example.sentence: They were so <highlight>busy</highlight> working that they only ate simple meals.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们忙于工作，只吃简单的饭菜。

examination_example.sentence: With such <highlight>busy</highlight> lives, it can be hard to try and find the time to work out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在如此忙碌的生活中，很难找到时间去锻炼。

examination_example.sentence: Charles Darwin imagined a world far <highlight>busier</highlight>, noisier and more intimate (亲密的) than the world we can see and hear.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 查尔斯·达尔文曾设想过一个比我们能看到和听到的世界更繁忙、更嘈杂、更亲密的世界。

examination_example.sentence: If you're <highlight>busy</highlight>, don't feel bad about saying no.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你很忙，不要因为拒绝别人而感到难受。
那将是一个繁忙的周末。

examination_example.sentence: She must be <highlight>busy</highlight> with her work.
The rabbit was very excited, and he was <highlight>busy</highlight> looking for the carrot, digging here and there.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 兔子很兴奋，他忙着找胡萝卜，到处挖来挖去。

examination_example.sentence: He is so <highlight>busy</highlight> that he hasn't had a good rest for several months.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他如此忙碌，以至于已经几个月没有好好休息了。

examination_example.sentence: A short drive later, we arrived at a <highlight>busy</highlight>, noisy factory.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 短暂的车程后，我们到了一个繁忙、嘈杂的工厂。

examination_example.sentence: We walked on the <highlight>busy</highlight> street, selling their creative pictures.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们走在热闹的街道上，出售他们的创意图片。

examination_example.sentence: We are a <highlight>busy</highlight> club with famous teachers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们是一个热闹的俱乐部，有著名的老师。

word_usage.usage:
说“某人工作忙”，应以人作主语。
示例：你工作很忙吗?

示例：She is busy doing/with her homework.
